To: J Meehan <j.meehan@huntington-ed.org.uk>
Cc: James Clarke <helpdesk@academia.co.uk>
Subject: ACTION: PC and Projector request in po2 and po3?

Hi Jonathan

I have had a few conversations with James about the computer and projector provision within the Drama department.

The laptops in both PO2 and po3 are causing problems with my team's day to day teaching as the laptops are proving to be pretty unpredictable. eg. when they turn on - sometimes class charts is missing or SIMs, or this morning the printer didn't link up.
From speaking with James a PC would hopefully prevent these unexpected issues from happening.

Also the projector that the Drama department bought many years ago is not great. It regularly freezes and the projection onto the wall is so faint we have to turn out the lights every time we want to use it.

Therefore please can I formally request that both laptops in po2 and po3 get replaced for pcs ( James informs me they are due to be replaced soon). Also can I request a new projector that can still be projected onto the large white wall in po2 only with a brighter image and one that is more predictable.

As a focus to develop our Drama provision for our VL students we are working hard to improve our use of PPT's within our lessons and so this will really help with this departmental development focus.

Any more information that you need, please let me know
Many thanks
Beth

injector for this purpose and the PoE injector will require a power socket
in the switch cabinet.

Dear All

*This is not a task or requirement but an additional CPD opportunity, being
shared as it may be of interest?*

NCFE, our independent assessment organisation and awarding body are
delivering a series of student conferences and next week one specifically
aimed at Education and childcare/EYFS students/apprentices. It is taking
place on Wednesday 8th February between 2-4pm.
It is focussed on '*Seeing the World through a Child's eyes.'*

*Please note: You don't need to watch it then, (I am aware some of you have
a training workshop taking place at the same time) but if you sign up for
it here,
<https://ncfemail.org.uk/ncfelz/lz.aspx?p1=MscDU2NzI0NlMzNzg6MEVDRUVEQjM4NTgyMDhCRkRGQzZGRjAwMEJCQ0NFRTk%3d-&CC=&w=18369>
you
will get the recording to watch at a time that suits you. *

By watching/attending you will get:

   - Insight into the importance of positive relationships in a child’s
   life for holistic, healthy, enabling opportunities that lay the foundation
   for future outcomes
   - A summary of the impact of the physical and relational environment
   against a pedagogical and theoretical framework
   - An opportunity to ask questions to our panel of subject specialists
   and professionals.


*Please see the email below forwarded for any further details.*

Best Wishes

Sue

*Virtual conference for your education and childcare learners *



Support your learners to improve their skills and knowledge with our free,
virtual CPD event focused on ‘seeing the world through a child’s eyes’.



This event is the second in our series of student conferences this year.
We’re excited for you and your learners to join us.

*Seeing the world through a child’s eyes*



Wednesday 8 February, 2pm–4pm

*Reserve your spot today
<https://ncfemail.org.uk/ncfelz/lz.aspx?p1=MscDU2NzI0NlMzNzg6MEVDRUVEQjM4NTgyMDhCRkRGQzZGRjAwMEJCQ0NFRTk%3d-&CC=&w=18365>*

   - Insight into the importance of positive relationships in a child’s
   life for holistic, healthy, enabling opportunities that lay the foundation
   for future outcomes
   - A summary of the impact of the physical and relational environment
   against a pedagogical and theoretical framework
   - An opportunity to ask questions to our panel of subject specialists
   and professionals.





You can share *this link
<https://ncfemail.org.uk/ncfelz/lz.aspx?p1=MscDU2NzI0NlMzNzg6MEVDRUVEQjM4NTgyMDhCRkRGQzZGRjAwMEJCQ0NFRTk%3d-&CC=&w=18369>*
with your learners if they wish to register individually. You’re also
welcome to register as a group to join us directly from your classroom!

your learners would like to receive a copy of the recording, we encourage
them to sign up individually, even if they join in a group setting on the
day.

*More from our student conferences*

learned at the event on *our website
